- Tenure neutrality advocates (3 papers): Policy should not favor particular tenures
- Financialization critics (7 papers): Credit-driven housing transformation creates inequality and instability
- Asset-based welfare analysts (4 papers): Homeownership increasingly substitutes for welfare provision
